Welcome and Thanks you.

This document will explain how to use and setup electric wire project.

  • Electric wire 1.4
  • Unity 2021.3.21f1 https://unity.com/

How to use electric wire

  • Open the SampleScene (Assets/ElectricWire/Scenes).

  • TAB key to switch cursor mode.

  • Select wire/component to build in the bar on the right.

  • To place a wire/component click left mouse, to cancel click right mouse.

  • Wire must start and end on a connector.

  • You can save and load your scene ingame (only wire and component).

  • Click the name to CLEAR scene and LOAD save data from file.

  • Click the X to DELETE file, no confirmation!

  • R / F to undo / redo.

  • Wind direction, wind force and sun angle can be adjusted.

How to setup component

  • In the folder (Assets/ElectricWire/Resources/Components).

  • Logic gate, counter, generator, lamp, switch, splitter, wire, ...

  • This image show the Switch as example.

  • When Energized the switch SetActive on a gameobject to show that the switch receive power.

  • When Turn On/Off the switch run a function on a gameobject to move the switch handle.

  • To create your own Component, derive your script from ElectricComponent.cs.

  • Is Energized value is On when the component is connected to a generator and that generator is turn On.

  • Is On value is On when the component is turn On. By player interaction or from another component signal.

  • Events are use to activate others gameobjects. This can be use to activate/deactivate gameobject in scene.

  • OnEnergized send true/false when component is energized.

  • OnTurnOnOff send true/false when component switch On/Off state.

  • OnTurnOnOffOnlyWhenEnergized send true/false when component switch On/Off state only if the component is energized.

  • WireConnectorInput store all input connector on this component.

  • WireConnectorOutput store all output connector on this component.

Managers

  • ElectricManager control placement and removal of component and wire.

  • ElectricRemoveManager to remove component and wire.

  • ElectricWireManager to place new wire from connector to connector.

  • ElectricComponentManager to place new component on surface.

  • Max undo / redo.

How to add electric wire to your project

  • Some project can require more complex or different setup.

  • ALWAYS BACKUP YOUR PROJECT BEFORE IMPORT NEW PACKAGE!

  • Import package.

  • Add ElectricManager.cs to your player and add the 3 prefabs from (Assets/ElectricWire/Prefabs/Managers).

  • Or use the Player.prefab (Assets/ElectricWire/Prefabs).

  • To have information on the current action, add ui text component in the InfoText field of ElectricManager component.

  • You can use the prefab PanelInfo.prefab (Assets/ElectricWire/Prefabs/_UI). Place it in your Canvas.

  • To use the 3 manager, call the function in ElectricManager.cs (the component on your player).

  • The objectPrefab parameter is the prefabs from (Assets/ElectricWire/Prefabs/Components) or (Assets/ElectricWire/Prefabs/Prebuilds).

  • ElectricManager.electricManager.OnClickRemoveButtonUI();

  • ElectricManager.electricManager.OnClickWireButtonUI(objectPrefab);

  • ElectricManager.electricManager.OnClickComponentButtonUI(objectPrefab);

  • Or you can use the PanelButton.prefab (Assets/ElectricWire/Prefabs/_UI).

  • Drag it in your Canvas. In this example the objectPrefab parameter is set in the Button event.

Component example

  • Again the switch as example.

  • Can be toggle On/Off.

  • 1 input (red) and 1 output (green).

  • You can setup 3 events.

  • When energized true/false.

  • When turn on/off.

  • When turn on/off only when energized.

  • Each connector must be set in the WireConnector Input/Output slot on the component.

  • Resize array to use more.

  • Input and output gameobject require the WireConnector.cs and a BoxCollider.
